{
  "domain": "airlines",
  "source_erd": "ground_truth_erd_B.json",
  "description": "Ground truth model for ERD-B, recorded as an element-to-canonical mapping. Its canonical vocabulary coincides with ERD-A's for the shared concepts (Passenger, Flight, Airline, Airplane, Airport), whose correspondences are induced by identical canonical names; where the two independent interpretations genuinely diverge (A's SeatAssignment vs B's Booking relator), the correspondence is asserted explicitly in cross_erd_ground_truth.json. Reference for scoring; not a competing method.",
  "canonical_vocabulary_aligned_with": "ground_truth_model_aligned.json (ERD-A): shared concepts share names; the Passenger x Flight relator diverges (SeatAssignment in A, Booking in B)",
